						<summary>

						<p>A slab built into the wall of a room, inside the prākāra of the temple of Venkaṭēśvara.</p>						

						<p>1600 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in Śaka 1522, Vikāri, Śrāvaṇa, ba. 13, Wednesday corresponding to 1600 A.D. August 26, f.d.t. 42.</p>						

						<p>Registers a grant of land made to the temple of Tiruvengaḷanātha of Injēḍu by a certain Akki Reḍḍi, situated at the entrance <hi rend="italic">(mogatala)</hi> of the village of Pinayama. He is stated to have consecrated the imagess of the goddess Śridēvi and the Āḷvārs therein.</p>						

						</summary>
